"title": "5738: sons",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5738",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The male offspring of parents. While sharing in the general privileges and responsibilities of children, sons had special claims to inheritance from their parents. To refer to Christians as “sons of God” is to identify both their relationship to God and also their rights as heirs of God. A significant number of titles for Jesus Christ make use of the term “Son”, stressing the close relationship between the Father and Son.</p>\n<h2>Privileges of sonship</h2>\n<h3>Inheritance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:22\">PRO 13:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:7\">GAL 4:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:2\">HEB 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Being disciplined</h3>\n<p>Discipline is here seen as a loving means of enabling a child to grow to maturity:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:5\">DEU 8:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:18\">PRO 19:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:17\">PRO 29:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:5-Heb12:11\">HEB 12:5–12:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:19\">REV 3:19</a></p>\n<h3>Being loved and provided for</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:11-Luke11:13\">LUK 11:11–11:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:9-Matt7:11\">MAT 7:9–7:11</a></p>\n<h3>Being prayed for</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:18-Gen17:20\">GEN 17:18–17:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:16\">2SA 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:5\">JOB 1:5</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of good sons</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:23\">GEN 9:23</a> <em>Shem and Japheth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:6-Gen22:12\">GEN 22:6–22:12</a> <em>Isaac</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen45:8-Gen45:11\">GEN 45:8–45:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen47:11-Gen47:12\">GEN 47:11–47:12</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:51\">LUK 2:51</a> <em>The voluntary obedience of the child Jesus towards Mary and Joseph is widely regarded as setting an example for believers.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:5\">2TI 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:14-2Tim3:15\">2TI 3:14–3:15</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of bad sons</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:1-Gen37:35\">GEN 37:1–37:35</a> <em>Jacob's eleven sons</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:11-Luke15:32\">LUK 15:11–15:32</a></p>\n<h2>Christians as sons of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:5-Heb12:6\">HEB 12:5–12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:14\">ROM 8:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:26\">ROM 9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:18\">2CO 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:7\">HEB 12:7</a></p>\n<h2>Adopted sons</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:10\">EXO 2:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:5\">GEN 48:5</a></p>\n<h2>Sons-in-law</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:12-Gen19:14\">GEN 19:12–19:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:5\">JDG 19:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:18-1Sam18:27\">1SA 18:18–18:27</a></p>\n<h2>Family relationships must be subservient to one's relationship with God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:35\">MAT 10:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:53\">LUK 12:53</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:37\">MAT 10:37</a></p>\n<h2>Son as an honorific term</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:2\">MAT 9:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:5\">MAT 9:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:31\">LUK 15:31</a></p>\n<h2>Sons in a spiritual role</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:18\">1TI 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:28\">JOL 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:17\">ACT 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:1\">2TI 1:1</a></p>\n<h2>Son in a non-literal sense</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:15\">MAT 23:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:17\">MRK 3:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:36\">JHN 12:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:36\">ACT 4:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:5\">1TH 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Titles of Jesus Christ as Son</h2>\n<h3>Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6\">ISA 9:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:7\">PSA 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:12\">PSA 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:17\">MAT 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:35\">JHN 3:35</a></p>\n<h3>Son of Joseph</h3>\n<p>Jesus Christ is described in this way by those who have yet to understand the circumstances of his conception and birth:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:23\">LUK 3:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:45\">JHN 1:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:42\">JHN 6:42</a></p>\n<h3>Son of Mary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:3\">MRK 6:3</a></p>\n<h3>Son of David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:22\">MAT 15:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:47-Mark10:48\">MRK 10:47–10:48</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:38-Luke18:39\">LUK 18:38–18:39</a></p>\n<h3>Son of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:20\">ACT 9:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:3\">MAT 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:35\">LUK 1:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:34\">JHN 1:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:7\">JHN 19:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:3-Rom1:4\">ROM 1:3–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:5\">1JN 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>Son of the living God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:16\">MAT 16:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Son of the Most High</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32\">LUK 1:32</a></p>\n<h3>Son of Man</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:10\">LUK 19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:20\">MAT 8:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:22\">MAT 17:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:12\">MRK 9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:22\">LUK 17:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:27\">JHN 5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:56\">ACT 7:56</a></p>",
